    "content": "<p>In a triangle $A B C$ as shown in the diagram, where $A B=5, A C=10$ and $B D=1$, then perimeter of $\\triangle A B C$ is</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m99elkbu/96da6a19-f2c8-4f7a-92a0-718b58a5dfa4/7f5b68a0-14f7-11f0-a266-23d4fe47bb6d/file-jaoe38c1m99elkbv.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m99elkbu/96da6a19-f2c8-4f7a-92a0-718b58a5dfa4/7f5b68a0-14f7-11f0-a266-23d4fe47bb6d/file-jaoe38c1m99elkbv.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"VITEEE 2024 Mathematics - Properties of Triangles Question 1 English\"></p>",
