    "explanation": "<p>$\\because A D$ divides $\\angle B A C$ is two equal parts.</p>\n<p>So, by angle bisector formula</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{B D}{D C}=\\frac{A B}{A C} \\Rightarrow \\frac{1}{D C}=\\frac{5}{10} \\\\\n\\Rightarrow \\quad & D C=2\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>Therefore, $B C=B D+D C=1+2=3$</p>\n<p>Hence, perimeter of $\\triangle A B C=A B+B C+C A$</p>\n<p>$$=5+3+10=18$$</p>",
